The paper deals with distributed channel quantization in interference networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers performance measures such as network outage probabilities, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes quantizer designs for transmission strategies, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper compares the proposed quantizers with conventional ones, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
